  "result": "Pool reuse open DB connections. No new connection per request. Skip TCP + auth handshake overhead.\n\nFlow: app borrow conn from pool → run query → return conn to pool. Conn stay alive, next req grab same one.\n\nKey params:\n- `min`/`max` size — idle floor, hard ceiling\n- `idle timeout` — kill stale conn\n- `acquire timeout` — fail fast when pool exhausted\n\nWin: lower latency, bounded DB load, no thundering herd of fresh handshakes.\n\nWatch: pool too small → req queue. Pool too big → DB conn limit hit. Long txn hog conn → starve others.",
